1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,002
[ mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,086 --> 00:00:03,462
[ penguins wenk ]

3
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,882
[ all cheering ]

4
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:11,011
[ screeches ]

5
00:00:13,389 --> 00:00:14,473
D> Adventure Time )

6
00:00:14,557 --> 00:00:16,475
» Come on, grab your friends »

7
00:00:16,559 --> 00:00:18,602
» We'll go to very distant lands J

8
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:20,729
» With Jake the Dog
and Finn the Human »

9
00:00:20,813 --> 00:00:22,356
D The fun will never end >

10
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,567
D It's Adventure Time »

11
00:00:32,825 --> 00:00:34,702
JAKE:
Beep! Beep! Look out.

12
00:00:34,785 --> 00:00:36,579
Beep! Beep!
Pillow delivery.

13
00:00:36,662 --> 00:00:39,081
Beep! Beep!
Look out, buddy!

14
00:00:39,165 --> 00:00:40,499
Ugh!

15
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:42,168
- BMO: Ugh!
- Come on, Jake.

16
00:00:42,251 --> 00:00:43,210
Sorry, buddy.

17
00:00:43,294 --> 00:00:45,796
I'm just trying
to cheer you up some.

18
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,382
| mean, here you are chilling
with history's coolest friends,

19
00:00:48,466 --> 00:00:50,092
building an actual
pillow fort,

20
00:00:50,176 --> 00:00:51,760
but you just sit there
sulking.

21
00:00:51,844 --> 00:00:53,179
I'm like, "what gives?"

22
00:00:53,262 --> 00:00:54,346
[ sighs ]

23
00:00:54,430 --> 00:00:56,390
| guess I'm just thinking
about Flame Princess.

24
00:00:56,474 --> 00:00:58,476
| told her
a joke the other day,

25
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:00,519
and she didn't even
laugh or anything.

26
00:01:00,603 --> 00:01:02,521
Guess it's over between us.

27
00:01:02,605 --> 00:01:04,398
That's it?
A joke?

28
00:01:04,482 --> 00:01:06,358
Maybe she just didn't
get it yet.

29
00:01:06,442 --> 00:01:07,902
Yeah, right, BMO.

30
00:01:07,985 --> 00:01:09,487
More like she used up
all her laughs

31
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,071
at some other guy's
jokes, probably.

32
00:01:11,155 --> 00:01:13,616
Man, having a girlfriend
is hard.

33
00:01:13,699 --> 00:01:16,243
No, being crazy
is hard.

34
00:01:16,327 --> 00:01:18,162
You're getting all hung up --

35
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:20,122
all hung up on imaginary
problems.

36
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:23,501
You got to focus on
what's real, man.

37
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:24,877
You see this cup?

38
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,254
This is literally
my favorite cup.

39
00:01:27,338 --> 00:01:28,797
Hunh!

40
00:01:28,881 --> 00:01:30,841
Now it's gone forever,
so it's not real,

41
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:32,760
and | don't care
about it anymore.

42
00:01:32,843 --> 00:01:35,429
[ gasps ] Oh, no!
My favorite window!

43
00:01:35,513 --> 00:01:38,891
| don't even know what
you guys are talking about.

44
00:01:38,974 --> 00:01:41,644
| think I just need
some alone time.

45
00:01:41,727 --> 00:01:44,230
Gotta let my mind fester
a bit, you know?

46
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:45,731
I'll be back
in a little while.

47
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:48,400
Finn, festering's
always bad, man!

48
00:01:48,484 --> 00:01:51,153
There's no good kind
of festering!

49
00:01:51,237 --> 00:01:52,905
Finn!!

50
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:55,824
Man.

51
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:58,244
This looks smaller
from the outside.

52
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:00,037
What's this, now?

53
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,123
What the...?
Jake, what's in here?

54
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:05,167
[ grunting ]
Jake?

55
00:02:05,251 --> 00:02:07,169
Ugh!

56
00:02:07,253 --> 00:02:08,462
Oh, whoa.

57
00:02:08,546 --> 00:02:10,381
[ birds chirping ]

58
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:12,424
Did Jake build this part, too?

59
00:02:12,508 --> 00:02:15,177
That guy needs some more
girlfriends or something.

60
00:02:15,261 --> 00:02:17,304
Hey, Jake?
You need more girlf--

61
00:02:17,388 --> 00:02:20,516
What the...?
Door's gone?

62
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,519
Hmmmmmm.

63
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:26,939
Maybe there's another door
in yonder pillow town.

64
00:02:30,901 --> 00:02:32,695
| don't get this at all.

65
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:34,280
Aah! Dragon! Run!

66
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:36,740
- Huh?
- Oof!

67
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:38,867
Hey, mister!
You better get running!

68
00:02:38,951 --> 00:02:39,952
Blanket dragon!

69
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:43,622
[ roaring ]

70
00:02:43,706 --> 00:02:46,041
Now, tAis, | understand.
Bwaah!

71
00:02:46,125 --> 00:02:48,377
[ roars ]

72
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,546
[ screaming ]

73
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,302
Oh. That's it?

74
00:02:56,385 --> 00:02:57,678
Wow!

75
00:02:57,761 --> 00:03:00,764
[ villagers cheering ]

76
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:02,808
Hey, uh...
how's it going?

77
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:04,685
Hoy, there!

78
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:08,063
I am Quilton,
son of Pillowford.

79
00:03:08,147 --> 00:03:11,942
And you have saved
our village!

80
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:15,237
You and your sharp pillow.

81
00:03:15,321 --> 00:03:17,740
[ chuckles ] It's nothing.
| kill things all the time.

82
00:03:17,823 --> 00:03:19,283
Oh, nonsense!

83
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:22,870
This calls
for a celepillobration!

84
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:24,705
Oh! [ laughs ]

85
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:27,833
[ up-tempo music plays,
indistinct conversations ]

86
00:03:36,675 --> 00:03:38,677
[ sighs ]

87
00:03:40,596 --> 00:03:42,056
There you are,
Finn the Human.

88
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:45,059
Oh. Hey... there.

89
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:48,479
Um... you can just
call me Finn, if you want.

90
00:03:48,562 --> 00:03:49,938
All right, Finn.

91
00:03:50,022 --> 00:03:52,524
My name is Roselinen,
daughter of Quilton.

92
00:03:52,608 --> 00:03:54,818
You have to call me
the whole thing.

93
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:55,986
Oh! U-Uhh...

94
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,446
[ chuckling ]
Just kidding.

95
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,406
[ laughs nervously ]
Oh!

96
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:01,241
Uh, your dad seems fun.

97
00:04:01,325 --> 00:04:03,827
[ laughing ]
Oh, my! Puhzah!

98
00:04:03,911 --> 00:04:05,704
[ chuckling ]
Yeah.

99
00:04:05,788 --> 00:04:07,831
Um... you want to dance?

100
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:09,875
Oh! Well...

101
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:11,877
... have a girlfriend.

102
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:12,961
[ chirps ]

103
00:04:13,045 --> 00:04:14,380
[ laughs ]

104
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:17,174
Dummy, it's a dance,
not marriage.

105
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,968
[ laughs nervously ]
Yeah. Okay.

106
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,972
This place is weird.

107
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:26,475
Are you telling me that birds
in yourworld

108
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:28,268
don't poo little
pillowcases?

109
00:04:28,352 --> 00:04:30,437
Nah -- just regular
poo.

110
00:04:30,521 --> 00:04:32,898
Hey -- like this.

111
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:37,486
[ clears throat ]

112
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:39,238
Yeah, i-it's really cool.

113
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:41,323
Where | come from,
| live with my best friend,

114
00:04:41,407 --> 00:04:42,741
who's my brother.

115
00:04:42,825 --> 00:04:44,076
And... he's a dog.
[ chuckles ]

116
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:45,744
We fight stuff.
It's cool.

117
00:04:45,828 --> 00:04:47,496
It's really different
than here.

118
00:04:47,579 --> 00:04:49,248
Um, where I'm from,
blankets and pillows

119
00:04:49,331 --> 00:04:50,457
are used for
bedding.

120
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:51,542
[ chuckles ]

121
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,752
Well, they're used for that
here, too.

122
00:04:53,836 --> 00:04:55,671
[ laughs nervously ]
Oh.

123
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:57,381
[ giggles ]

124
00:04:57,464 --> 00:04:58,882
Pillightful!

125
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:00,718
Aw, man.
It's been nice, Roselinen,

126
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,344
but | got to get back
to my home.

127
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:05,097
Quilton, | need your help
to find the portal to my home world.

128
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:07,933
Of course we will do our best
to help you,

129
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,893
Finn the Flesh Pillow,

130
00:05:09,977 --> 00:05:13,689
but you're not
making a fold of sense.

131
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:16,650
Please -- share our food.

132
00:05:16,734 --> 00:05:18,610
You need nourishment.

133
00:05:18,694 --> 00:05:20,612
[ chomping ]

134
00:05:20,696 --> 00:05:23,115
[ muffled ]
It tastes like a pillow.

135
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:27,619
I'll give your compliments
to the pillow.

136
00:05:27,703 --> 00:05:30,372
[ thunder rumbles ]

137
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,878
Oh. There you are.
You found your mug.

138
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:38,964
| thought you said
you didn't care.

139
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,674
[ sips ]

140
00:05:40,758 --> 00:05:42,593
That mug is empty.

141
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:45,387
| wonder
what Finn's up to.

142
00:05:45,471 --> 00:05:48,807
Roar!
I'm the blanket dragon!

143
00:05:48,891 --> 00:05:51,518
Well, /'m daddy!
Sha-pow!

144
00:05:51,602 --> 00:05:52,936
Jay, Bonnie,
| bet your daddy

145
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:54,980
is just about finished
chopping wool.

146
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:56,815
You guys want to bring him
his lunch?

147
00:05:56,899 --> 00:05:58,609
BOTH:
Yes!

148
00:05:58,692 --> 00:06:00,694
[ grunting ]

149
00:06:03,906 --> 00:06:05,866
[ laughing in deep voice ]

150
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,326
Alphanumeric!

151
00:06:07,409 --> 00:06:10,996
Pillow Sheep, you have more
fluff than sense.

152
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,539
Mwah!

153
00:06:12,623 --> 00:06:14,082
BOTH:
Daddy! Daddy!

154
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:15,959
[ laughs ]

155
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:19,254
What is this -- a pack of
fearsome pillow goblins?

156
00:06:19,338 --> 00:06:22,591
[ laughing ]
Daddy! We're your kids!

157
00:06:22,674 --> 00:06:24,676
Psst! Finn!
They've brought you lunch.

158
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:26,845
Oh, they have,
have they?

159
00:06:26,929 --> 00:06:29,515
Tiny pillows.
Mmm!

160
00:06:29,598 --> 00:06:30,933
[ chuckles ]

161
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:33,685
Darling, you've outdone
yourself.

162
00:06:33,769 --> 00:06:35,145
Honk! Honk!

163
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:36,313
BOTH:
Grandpillow!

164
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:37,856
What's my father doing here?

165
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:38,857
Pbht!

166
00:06:38,941 --> 00:06:40,400
Oh, Puhoy!

167
00:06:40,484 --> 00:06:41,860
BOTH:
Grandpillow!

168
00:06:41,944 --> 00:06:42,861
Grandpillow!

169
00:06:42,945 --> 00:06:44,238
Oh! Come here!

170
00:06:44,321 --> 00:06:47,574
But... I've come to speak
with your father.

171
00:06:47,658 --> 00:06:48,575
What is it, Quilton?

172
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:50,661
When you first arrived here,

173
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:53,872
you told us
of a mysterious door

174
00:06:53,956 --> 00:06:56,875
that led you to our world.

175
00:06:56,959 --> 00:06:58,836
Yes. Of course.

176
00:06:58,919 --> 00:07:03,549
Archeologists found this in
the pillow catacombs --

177
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:05,884
the Pillownomicon.

178
00:07:05,968 --> 00:07:07,469
Oh, my glob.

179
00:07:07,553 --> 00:07:10,180
There is no information
about the door,

180
00:07:10,264 --> 00:07:13,725
save for the fact it
shows up periodically

181
00:07:13,809 --> 00:07:15,477
and then disappears.

182
00:07:15,561 --> 00:07:19,064
Quilton, | need to find
that door.

183
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:23,277
Uhh... hey, BMO,

184
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,612
I-I gotta snag my mug
from you.

185
00:07:25,696 --> 00:07:27,364
Oh. Really?

186
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,615
Hey, don't sweat it.

187
00:07:28,699 --> 00:07:30,033
I'll make us some
hot chocolate.

188
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:33,245
Jake, you drive a hard
burger.

189
00:07:36,248 --> 00:07:37,124
Hello?

190
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:40,127
Ah, yes. Come in.

191
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:43,297
Are these the great
Abba-cadabra Mountains?

192
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:45,424
And are you Rasheeta,
the great Oracle,

193
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:47,342
dweller of said
mountains?

194
00:07:47,426 --> 00:07:51,096
Yes. And you must be Finn,
the Human Man,

195
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:53,932
seeker of the wandering
portal.

196
00:07:54,016 --> 00:07:56,393
Yes. Yes, I-I've searched
for decades.

197
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,936
How did you know?

198
00:07:58,020 --> 00:08:00,480
| read it
in the tea leaves.

199
00:08:00,564 --> 00:08:03,400
This newspaper | found
from the future.

200
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:05,193
Does it say
how | get home?

201
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:08,655
The real question is, are you
sure you wantto?

202
00:08:08,739 --> 00:08:10,657
Uhh... yeah.

203
00:08:10,741 --> 00:08:13,285
Well, don't worry.
You won't be here long.

204
00:08:13,368 --> 00:08:14,369
[ farts ]

205
00:08:14,453 --> 00:08:16,788
So, there's another way to --
Oof!

206
00:08:16,872 --> 00:08:19,124
Not long now.
[ farts ]

207
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:22,294
Ooh!
[ coughs ]

208
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,755
[ coughing ]

209
00:08:26,882 --> 00:08:27,841
Father!

210
00:08:27,925 --> 00:08:29,801
What did the oracle say,
father?

211
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:31,678
Have we come to the right spot
finally?

212
00:08:31,762 --> 00:08:35,432
| think so, but the oracle
spoke in riddles.

213
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:38,352
Gonna have to fester
on this one for a bit --

214
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:39,811
Oh, Finn.

215
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:41,521
| know you have to go.

216
00:08:41,605 --> 00:08:43,649
All these years,
I've known.

217
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:45,567
But now that it's time...

218
00:08:45,651 --> 00:08:47,819
[ sniffles ]
Oh, man.

219
00:08:47,903 --> 00:08:50,656
I'm just
all messed up about it.

220
00:08:50,739 --> 00:08:53,158
Just promise me
you'll remember us

221
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,702
when you're back
in your real life.

222
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:57,371
Hmm.

223
00:08:57,454 --> 00:08:59,748
That reminds me, Roselinen, of
something Jake told me

224
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:01,875
just before | came
to this world.

225
00:09:01,959 --> 00:09:03,961
[ distorted ]
You're getting all hung up

226
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:06,004
on imaginary problems.

227
00:09:06,088 --> 00:09:08,215
Stay with your new wife.

228
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:10,634
You've known her longer now
than any of us.

229
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,553
You're not even sure /ever
really existed.

230
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:17,015
And I'm pretty sure | didn't
look like this.

231
00:09:17,099 --> 00:09:18,767
Man.

232
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:21,019
How did he see it all coming
so clearly?

233
00:09:21,103 --> 00:09:22,854
Come on, everyone.
Pack your things.

234
00:09:22,938 --> 00:09:24,731
We're going home.

235
00:09:24,815 --> 00:09:26,733
[ giggling ]

236
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:28,110
Goodness, Jake.

237
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:30,737
Why don't you do this
with your other babies?

238
00:09:30,821 --> 00:09:33,281
Well, Rainicorn babies
age rapidly.

239
00:09:33,365 --> 00:09:36,618
They don't need their parents
a couple hours after they're born.

240
00:09:36,702 --> 00:09:38,412
That really stinks, huh?

241
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:40,080
Mm...

242
00:09:40,163 --> 00:09:43,625
[ bell dings ]
Hot chocolate is ready!

243
00:09:43,709 --> 00:09:45,794
ROSELINEN:
Finn? Finn!

244
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:47,504
RVECELOA!
Wha-- where?

245
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:48,714
Are you comfortable?

246
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,966
I'm... all right.

247
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:52,467
Um... Dad?

248
00:09:52,551 --> 00:09:54,386
[ voice breaking ]
Dad, we just wanted...

249
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:56,471
to say that... we --

250
00:09:56,555 --> 00:09:58,056
[ sobs ]

251
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:00,183
That... we love you, Dad.

252
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:04,813
| remember back
when /was dad.

253
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:07,816
[ sighs ]
Dad, you are Dad.

254
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:09,735
| ain't Dad yet!

255
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:11,945
Oh. No.
Wait!

256
00:10:12,029 --> 00:10:13,780
Here it comes!

257
00:10:13,864 --> 00:10:17,617
Oh!
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo, boy!

258
00:10:20,287 --> 00:10:21,246
Oh!

259
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:23,415
Hup!

260
00:10:33,341 --> 00:10:35,343
Hey, buddy.
You feeling better already?

261
00:10:35,427 --> 00:10:37,054
Huh? Oh.

262
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,680
Uhh... I don't know, man.

